data.database_description: The described database schema is designed to manage a customer service and lesson booking system. It tracks customer information, including their addresses and payment details, while also recording staff members, vehicles, and lessons conducted. The relationships between tables are established through foreign keys, ensuring data integrity and enabling efficient querying of interconnected information, such as which staff member taught a specific lesson or the address of a particular customer.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each address.
The first line of the address, including number and building name.
The city where the address is located.
The zip code or postal code for the address.
The state, province, or county where the address is located.
The country where the address is located.

sample_data: 1, 3904 Stroman Passage, Port Melyssa, 14445, Georgia, USA
3, 00704 Zoe Alley, Lake Elaina, 08938, Oregon, USA
enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores address information for customers and staff members.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each staff member.
Foreign key referencing the address of the staff member.
A nickname or informal name for the staff member.
The first name of the staff member.
The middle name of the staff member.
The last name of the staff member.
The date of birth of the staff member.
The date when the staff member joined the organization.
The date when the staff member left the organization.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about staff members, including their personal details and employment history.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each vehicle.
Description or type of the vehicle (e.g., Van, Truck).

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores details about vehicles available for lessons.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for the customer.
Foreign key linking to the address of the customer.
Code representing the status of the customer (e.g., Good Customer, Bad Customer).
Date when the customer became a member.
Customer's date of birth.
Customer's first name.
Customer's last name.
Amount the customer owes, if any.
Customer's email address.
Customer's phone number.
Customer's mobile phone number.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores customer information including personal details and financial status.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for the customer.
Date and time when the payment was made.
Code representing the method used for payment (e.g., Direct Debit, Credit Card).
Amount of the payment made.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about payments made by customers.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each lesson.
Identifier linking the lesson to a specific customer.
Status of the lesson (e.g., Completed, Cancelled).
Identifier linking the lesson to the staff member who conducted it.
Identifier linking the lesson to the vehicle used.
Date when the lesson took place or was scheduled.
Time when the lesson took place or was scheduled.
Cost of the lesson.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Records information about each lesson including customer details, staff member, vehicle used, and pricing.
